casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellant, v. Ginley, Appellee.

[Cite as State v. Ginley, 130 Ohio St.3d 1214, 2011-Ohio-5447.]

(No. 2010-1925 Submitted October 4, 2011 Decided October 26, 2011.) William D. Mason, Cuyahoga County Prosecuting Attorney, and Matthew Meyer, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellant. Susan J. Moran, for appellee. Robert L. Tobik and John T. Martin, urging dismissal or affirmance for amicus curiae, Cuyahoga County Public Defender.

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently accepted.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Cupp, and McGee Brown, JJ., concur.
